The paper deals with the coordinated motion of a collection of agents, which is a typical problem in multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also uses tools from graph theory and combinatorics to analyze the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves planning and optimization, which are common themes in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO).
